description:
&lt;p&gt;If you are student nurse looking to gain extra experience, work around your studies and earn a bit of extra cash the LTHT Staff Bank has a great opportunity for you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;About the Role:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Trust: &lt;/strong&gt;Leeds Teaching Hospitals&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;Leeds - Trust Wide&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Wards Covered: &lt;/strong&gt;General&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pay: &lt;/strong&gt;Band 2&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;- Days:  £9.89 - £10.19 per hour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;- Saturday/Nights: £14.04 - £14.48 per hour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;- Sunday/Bank Holiday: £18.20 -£18.88 per hour&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We have new enhanced rates across all ESM, J09, J10, J11, J12, J43 and Adult Crit Care:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Days: £14.24&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Saturday/Nights - £18.39&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sunday/Bank Holiday- £22.55&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking compassionate, enthusiastic and motivated student nurses  who are wating to gain more experience to work within Leeds Teaching Hospitals. A successful candidate will be an effective team player and will be committed to equal opportunities and non-discriminatory practices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, as a care assistant, you will be working closely with multi-disciplinary team members to provide a high standard of care for patients throughout their visit or stay at Leeds Teaching Hospitals. You will be responsible for implementing treatment and risk management plans and aiding patients through their recovery. Moreover, you will also be responsible for providing support and comfort to patient family members or carers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;During your work as a care assistant, you will be expected to provide a high level of care to all patients in your ward or clinical area. This may include (and will not be limited to) moving and handling, cleaning and bathing patients, feeding patients and patient observations – this could be for a wide variety of patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits of Staff Bank:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Weekly Pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salary - £9.89 - £22.55&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;First choice of all available shifts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;24 hour bookings service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexibility to suit your lifestyle&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Holiday pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to book your shifts online&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pension&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free uniform and mandatory training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Trust pay incentives and bonuses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Long term placements available&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free Fast track DBS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A successful candidate for this Health Care Assistant role will have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2nd or 3rd year Student Nursing student.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full vaccination history (must include full course of Hepatitis B vaccinations and blood test, 2 MMR vaccinations, a BCG vaccination).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work a minimum of 1 shifts every 3 months.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pass pre-employment checks (including enhanced DBS, occupational health screening and entitlement to work checks).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Recruitment Process:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1.       &lt;/strong&gt;Online ‘XChecker’ form&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2.       &lt;/strong&gt;Informal 20 minute video interview&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;3.       &lt;/strong&gt;Remote Compliance Checks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(Please note, it may take 3-6 weeks to complete pre-employment checks)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please apply for the Clinical Support Worker role here, or give our Recruitment Team a call on &lt;strong&gt;020 816 72491&lt;/strong&gt; for more information or to apply (Mon-Fri 8am-5:30pm).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
